dmap2023.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022947\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-10T13:33:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223538079\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549804795\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA long time ago, when KSP was 0.1x...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think \u003Cem\u003Ethey \u003C/em\u003Estill have that as their hab design.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-10T13:52:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223538084\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549805581\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DDE\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, DDE said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think \u003Cem\u003Ethey \u003C/em\u003Estill have that as their hab design.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat was Mars One, so unlikely \u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E(.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut KSP remembers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022maxresdefault.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vinCXpnWY8A/maxresdefault.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starman4308","CreatedById":122674,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-10T14:21:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223538048\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549797504\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey may\u00A0revive the old idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022mercury-space-station.gif?w=584\u0026amp;h=357\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022358\u0022 src=\u0022https://falsesteps.files.wordpress.com/2012/11/mercury-space-station.gif?w=584\u0026amp;h=357\u0022 width=\u0022584\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Then we need Infernal Robotics to mod)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat... actually gives me an idea. I\u0027d been assuming a Dragon mounted in the top, with a pyrotechnically separated panel in case it needed to separate in a hurry. But what if... we bolted a Dragon to the\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eside\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0of the Starship? Relatively minimal modifications to the Starship, less damage to the Starship if the Dragon separates in a low-stress environment (such as if the Starship heat shield isn\u0027t fully trusted yet)...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027d play havoc with the aerodynamics, yes, but with the sheer excess of payload capacity and non-trivial gimbaling capacity on the Superheavy, it might be doable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-10T16:17:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223538022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549793050\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDragon has an integrated service module in lower part.\u00A0\u00A0Now add that the side of starship and the escape pod not the bottom will be heated during normal reentry.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s the problem -- how to create an escape capsule that still works in nominal entry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-10T16:48:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223538160\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549815450\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s the problem -- how to create an escape capsule that still works in nominal entry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHm. With such a challenge, my old gal the Martin 410 comes to mind.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022martin-410-cutaway-diagram.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022622\u0022 src=\u0022https://falsesteps.files.wordpress.com/2012/10/martin-410-cutaway-diagram.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you use two of such lifting body RVs, you\u2019d only need to replace the ablator on one following a nominal entry - or perhaps you could even equip them with a non-perishable TPS of some kind, and/or link them to the main Starship coolant loop.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinally, if you don\u2019t mind completely losing the Starship after \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Launch Escape System\u0022\u003ELES\u003C/abbr\u003E activation, locating all of your pods on the leeward side, with their single-use ablator inside the main hull, is probably the best option.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-10T17:47:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XcTpKi1DtpOmnfxouBuTRtxpsvLNYR0NLQpTpMZp\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022535\u0022 src=\u0022https://external-preview.redd.it/XcTpKi1DtpOmnfxouBuTRtxpsvLNYR0NLQpTpMZpf1I.jpg?width=1200\u0026amp;height=628.272251309\u0026amp;auto=webp\u0026amp;s=ab8ef7c67ea7db1c31c362d467736215c1c846c5\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother view:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022BFR-01c-513x536.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022536\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.teslarati.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/BFR-01c-513x536.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022513\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder...if we imagine ripping that giant hatch off entirely? The \u0022crew Starship\u0022 would comprise a standard cargo LV with a drop-in hab and crew vehicle, with no other modifications to the OML. A vehicle could be validated for crew launch by multiple cargo launches and then \u0022retired\u0022 back to cargo service only once a certain number of crew launches were completed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith that kind of volume, I wonder if a wider (8-9 meter) Dream Chaser style crew vehicle, mounted inside that space, would be workable. Somewhere between Dream Chaser and a truncated version of the \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.astronautix.com/a/apollolenticular.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Elenticular Apollo design\u003C/a\u003E. The forward canards of Starship could even be incorporated as the wings of the escape capsule for passive stability at abort.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rakaydos","CreatedById":101988,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-10T18:24:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223538201\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549820835\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n33 minutes ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://external-preview.redd.it/XcTpKi1DtpOmnfxouBuTRtxpsvLNYR0NLQpTpMZpf1I.jpg?width=1200\u0026amp;height=628.272251309\u0026amp;auto=webp\u0026amp;s=ab8ef7c67ea7db1c31c362d467736215c1c846c5\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XcTpKi1DtpOmnfxouBuTRtxpsvLNYR0NLQpTpMZp\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022535\u0022 src=\u0022https://external-preview.redd.it/XcTpKi1DtpOmnfxouBuTRtxpsvLNYR0NLQpTpMZpf1I.jpg?width=1200\u0026amp;height=628.272251309\u0026amp;auto=webp\u0026amp;s=ab8ef7c67ea7db1c31c362d467736215c1c846c5\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother view:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022BFR-01c-513x536.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022536\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.teslarati.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/BFR-01c-513x536.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022513\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder...if we imagine ripping that giant hatch off entirely? The \u0022crew Starship\u0022 would comprise a standard cargo LV with a drop-in hab and crew vehicle, with no other modifications to the OML. A vehicle could be validated for crew launch by multiple cargo launches and then \u0022retired\u0022 back to cargo service only once a certain number of crew launches were completed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith that kind of volume, I wonder if a wider (8-9 meter) Dream Chaser style crew vehicle, mounted inside that space, would be workable. Somewhere between Dream Chaser and a truncated version of the \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.astronautix.com/a/apollolenticular.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Elenticular Apollo design\u003C/a\u003E. The forward canards of Starship could even be incorporated as the wings of the escape capsule for passive stability at abort.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds reasonable, if you ignore the elephant in the room for any abort system. What kind of explosive bolts work when you need it, but not when the thing they\u0027re attached to is 1200 degrees? The Hot Structure design (where needed heat shield performance is reduced by using structural members as a heat sink) means SPaceX is using pure mechanical systems... but can a mechanical system be fast enough to handle an abort scenerio?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-10T18:40:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet me suggest a probably new idea of a mass escape system for BFS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, the BFS nose contains a passenger\u00A0cabin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet\u0027s make a pole along\u00A0the cabin longitudal axis, and\u00A0attach the individual seats radially to the pole with\u00A0individual hinges, so they can always align along the acceleration vector.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen something happens, we uncover the top of the cabin, and ignite the spin engines.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe pole starts quickly rotating.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022hqdefault.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022360\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hoIlZMKz1_o/hqdefault.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnce the pole is rotating enough fast, we detach the seats from the pole, so they get safely spread out of the cabin by the centrifugal force. Then they use individual chutes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe can name it Rotary Escape System.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-02-10T18:41:08Z\u0022 title=\u002202/10/2019 06:41  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 10, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-10T19:18:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223538218\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549823066\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022101988\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rakaydos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n35 minutes ago, Rakaydos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds reasonable, if you ignore the elephant in the room for any abort system. What kind of explosive bolts work when you need it, but not when the thing they\u0027re attached to is 1200 degrees? The Hot Structure design (where needed heat shield performance is reduced by using structural members as a heat sink) means SPaceX is using pure mechanical systems... but can a mechanical system be fast enough to handle an abort scenerio?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNotionally, the contingency abort vehicle would be mated to the remainder of the cabin module in much the same way that Dream Chaser was to mate to the top of an Atlas V or to the ISS: through the tail. Other connections, like the external hydraulic loops and prop feed lines, would have standard breakaway valves. The abort vehicle would contain head pressure bottles\u00A0topped by the main system loops to fuel \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E (for nominal mission use) and hot-gas meth-ox thrusters for escape, ignited in the same way as the Raptors. 300 m/s should be enough.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the forward canards double as wings, they can cock back for stability and then use thrusters or splashdown for landing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rakaydos","CreatedById":101988,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-10T19:23:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223538238\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549826295\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNotionally, the contingency abort vehicle would be mated to the remainder of the cabin module in much the same way that Dream Chaser was to mate to the top of an Atlas V or to the ISS: through the tail. Other connections, like the external hydraulic loops and prop feed lines, would have standard breakaway valves. The abort vehicle would contain head pressure bottles\u00A0topped by the main system loops to fuel \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E (for nominal mission use) and hot-gas meth-ox thrusters for escape, ignited in the same way as the Raptors. 300 m/s should be enough.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the forward canards double as wings, they can cock back for stability and then use thrusters or splashdown for landing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh. And here I thought you were describing a simple \u0022crew payload module\u0022 for the chomper. the problems of which center on getting the chomper door out of the way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut now it seems you\u0027re going back to the \u0022saw Starship in half and make 1 of the halves a mini starship\u0022 plan.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-10T20:48:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223538242\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549826633\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022101988\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rakaydos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Rakaydos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh. And here I thought you were describing a simple \u0022crew payload module\u0022 for the chomper. the problems of which center on getting the chomper door out of the way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut now it seems you\u0027re going back to the \u0022saw Starship in half and make 1 of the halves a mini starship\u0022 plan.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot at all. It\u0027s definitely still \u0022crew payload module for the chomper\u0022 but with the the \u0022chomper door\u0022 problem eliminated by detaching the chomper door altogether and making the escape portion of the crew payload (the \u0022Dragon 3\u0022) integrate with the vehicle OML.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-11T01:39:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFeel like this fits better in this thread. I came across it in the SpaceX facebook group - I only started reading it, fyi.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8203225079\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://www.reddit.com/r/spacex/comments/ap3bz1/estimating_the_mass_of_a_martian_propellant_plant/\u0022 style=\u0022height:12960px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nothalogh","CreatedById":139345,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-17T01:06:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223525887\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548032171\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/20/2019 at 7:56 PM, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt missing parts like an escape system\u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo did STS and Gemini\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-17T03:57:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223538201\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549820835\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/11/2019 at 12:47 AM, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder...if\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E we imagine ripping that giant hatch off entirely?\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223538218\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549823066\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022101988\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rakaydos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/11/2019 at 1:24 AM, Rakaydos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E kind of explosive bolts work when you need it, but not when the thing they\u0027re attached to is 1200 degrees?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was going to suggest an even crazier method \u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EThe entire hinged section\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eis\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0the manned compartment.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-19T12:31:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223561445\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552795051\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YNM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/16/2019 at 11:57 PM, YNM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was going to suggest an even crazier method \u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EThe entire hinged section\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eis\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0the manned compartment.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith or without the hinge?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-19T12:56:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA collapsible habitat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00225196s0\u002BvSlL._UX522_.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022522\u0022 src=\u0022https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/I/5196s0\u002BvSlL._UX522_.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022522\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-19T12:57:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223563060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552998671\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith or without the hinge?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EWith\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf anything goes wrong,\u00A0 you just have to undo the hinge - and that\u0027s it, abandon ship.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-19T14:14:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223563072\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221553000245\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YNM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, YNM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EWith\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf anything goes wrong,\u00A0 you just have to undo the hinge - and that\u0027s it, abandon ship.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou need extra rockets for 0-0 abort.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou also need a single-use ablative heat shield underneath the hinged portion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou need a way to break the hinge and blow free of the front end of the ship, because it comes up in a lip.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf your entire crew section is the capsule, then you need massive chutes large enough to land it safely; if not, then you need an internal interface to get into the permanent portion of the ship, but ones that can be severed instantly in an abort.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll of it is verrrry nontrivial.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-19T15:01:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223563107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221553004849\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n53 minutes ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nrockets... single-use ablative heat shield... break the hinge \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Eand blow free of the front end of the ship... massive chutes...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll of it is verrrry nontrivial.\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, all of those will be needed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, I didn\u0027t say they\u0027re\u00A0trivial matter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I suppose it highlights the difficulties in truly making mass launch of people into space to be a normal thing. We already freaked out because 346 people died from 2 crashes out of 376 airplanes, all of which combined already conducted hundreds of dozens of flight, probably carrying hundreds of thousands of people - that gives a ballpark of 99.9% reliability per passenger.\u00A0Would we accept lower reliability for manned spaceflight ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-19T15:08:10Z\u0022 title=\u002203/19/2019 03:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 19, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by YNM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-19T22:20:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223563152\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221553007683\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YNM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, YNM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, all of those will be needed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, I didn\u0027t say they\u0027re\u00A0trivial matter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I suppose it highlights the difficulties\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E i\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003En truly making mass launch of people into space to be a normal thing. We already freaked out because 346 people died from 2 crashes out of 376 airplanes, all of which combined already conducted hundreds of dozens of flight, probably carrying hundreds of thousands of people - that gives a ballpark of 99.9% reliability per passenger.\u00A0Would we accept lower reliability for manned spaceflight ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the next 25 years yes, as we know its an high risk activity similar to climbing Mont Everest.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nAll know that mountain climbing is dangerous, same with many other high risk sports.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAirplanes on the other hand are supposed to be safe.\u003Cbr\u003E\nNote that an lack of an crew escape system is my main issue with the Starship. Yes I know it has B-52 level engine out capabilities, but an crash of the dear moon project will hurt.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nBut main objective as in starlink will not be much impacted by this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}